#API DOCUMENTATION 

# User API

## Get Logged-in User Profile

Returns the profile information of the currently authenticated user.

### Endpoint

```
GET /api/users/profile
```

### Base URL

```
http://localhost:5000/api
```

### Authentication

Required (JWT Bearer Token)

### Headers

| Key           | Value            |
| ------------- | ---------------- |
| Authorization | Bearer JWT_TOKEN |

### Success Response

**Status Code:** `200 OK`

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "user": {
    "_id": "...",
    "name": "Test User",
    "email": "test@example.com",
    "role": "entrepreneur"
  }
}
```

### Possible Responses

| Status | Description                  |
| ------ | ---------------------------- |
| 200    | Profile fetched successfully |
| 401    | Unauthorized                 |
| 404    | User not found               |
| 500    | Internal server error        |

### Features

* Returns authenticated user's profile.
* Used by AuthContext after login.
* Verifies JWT before returning data.

---

## Update User Profile

Updates the authenticated user's profile.

### Endpoint

```
PUT /api/users/profile
```

### Authentication

Required

### Request Body

```json
{
  "bio":"Building AI Startup",
  "location":"Pakistan",
  "website":"https://example.com",
  "industry":"AI"
}
```

### Features

* Updates entrepreneur/investor profile.
* Supports profile completion.
* Saves profile changes in MongoDB.

